  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; two factors (Test conditions, Model inputs) marginally below required level. The assessment team determined that the shortfall is insufficient to support acceptance at modelRiskLevel 3 without additional evidence; the decision is therefore Not accepted pending supplementary testing under the missing load condition.",
