        "description": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of the same Ti-6Al-4V lot; geometric dimensions from CMM measurement of production screws. Gradation 3 requires probabilistic characterisation of all influential inputs with documented uncertainty bounds; Gradation 2 requires nominal values with identified sources. Achieved Gradation 2 only — coupon-level material variability not propagated to model inputs."
      },
      "rationale": "Nominal elastic modulus (114 GPa) and yield strength (880 MPa) were assigned from lot-specific coupon data (n=5 tensile specimens). However, the within-lot variability of material properties was not propagated into the FEA input deck as a probabilistic distribution; only point estimates were used. Gradation 3 requires documented uncertainty bounds on all influential inputs, which was not achieved. Achieved level: 2. Required level for modelRiskLevel 3: 3. This shortfall is one of two factors driving the Not-accepted decision."
