        "description": "Testing performed under ASTM F1717 standard protocol at a single compressive load angle (5°). Gradation 3 requires testing under multiple physiologically relevant load conditions to bound the COU; Gradation 2 requires a single standardised test condition. Only the ASTM F1717 standard angle was applied — a second load angle representing lateral bending was not included. Achieved Gradation 2 only."
      },
      "rationale": "All experimental constructs were tested at the single 5° off-axis compression angle specified by ASTM F1717. The COU encompasses compression-bending prediction for the implanted device, which may experience combined bending planes in vivo. Gradation 3 requires at least two load conditions spanning the physiological envelope; the absence of a lateral bending test case constrains the validation evidence to a single load path. Achieved level: 2. Required level for modelRiskLevel 3: 3. This is the primary shortfall driving the Not-accepted decision."
